    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - TURBOCHARGERS - REMOVAL AND INSPECTION</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVAL AND INSPECTION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="5">
            <title>Turbocharger Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using an open end wrench, loosen and remove oil feed supply tube nut located on top of
                    oil filter header. Remove and discard tube nut O-Ring. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050206">2.6</hotlnk>.
                    </emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two capcrew securing oil feed supply tube to top of turbocharger housing. Refer
                    to
                    <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050207">2.7</hotlnk>.
                    </emph>
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050206" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1722" filename="../figeg1/EG1722.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>FIGURE 2.6.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Oil Filter Header</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Oil Feed Supply Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Oil Feed Supply Tube Nut</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050207" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1969" filename="../figeg1/EG1969.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>FIGURE 2.7.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Turbocharger Assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Capscrews (2)</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Oil Feed Supply Tube</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil feed supply tube and tube flange gasket from turbocharger assembly. Discard
                    flange gasket. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050208">2.8</hotlnk>.
                    </emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cap oil feed supply tube fitting located on filter header. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050209">2.9</hotlnk>.
                    </emph>
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050208" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1975" filename="../figeg1/EG1975.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>FIGURE 2.8.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Oil Feed Supply Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Turbocharger Assembly</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050209" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1737" filename="../figeg1/EG1737.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>FIGURE 2.9.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Oil Filter Header</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Oil Feed Supply Tube Fitting</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Protective Cap</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove turbocharger oil drain tube as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050210">2.10</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    )
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen capscrew securing turbocharger oil drain tube retaining plate to crankcase.
                        Remove retaining plate and capscrew.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two capscrews securing turbocharger oil drain tube to bottom of turbocharger
                        housing.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove turbocharger oil drain tube retaining plate together with turbo oil drain
                        tube, tube flange, two tube O-Rings and tube flange gasket from bottom of turbocharger assembly.
                        Discard both drain tube O-Rings (one on each end of drain tube) and flange gasket.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cap
                    <emph type="bold">ALL</emph>
                    openings on the turbocharger assembly.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If plastic caps are
                            <emph type="underscr">not</emph>
                            available, use duct tape to cover openings.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1050210" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1724" filename="../figeg1/EG1724.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>FIGURE 2.10.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube Flange Gasket</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Turbocharger Assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Oil Drain Tube Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube Retaining Plate</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube Flange Gasket</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four capscrews securing turbocharger assembly to exhaust manifold flange. Refer
                    to
                    <emph type="bold">FIGURE
                        <hotlnk document="e105_34.xml" xrefid="ef1050211">2.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>Remove turbocharger assembly and gasket from engine. Discard gasket.</para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>SUPPORT TURBOCHARGER ASSEMBLY DURING REMOVAL OF MOUNTING HARDWARE TO PREVENT DAMAGE.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
